## 4. North-star distance
(on-vector / advancing / diverging, in which dimension, with evidence + confidence)

**On-vector** (confidence high), in the **instrument-honesty / Q5 dimension** — and the first arc to make a concrete down-payment on it, while still not yet touching the phenomenon (Q1-Q4, Obs7).

Will's frozen Q5 is the one that stops him: "Is the structure a real property of the phenomenon, or an artefact of the measurement?… instrument and object may be entangled and I have no way to separate 'this is real' from 'this is the measurement.'" (`where_i_got_stuck.md` L117-128). This arc is the substrate's first operational encounter with exactly that failure mode, at the AlphaProbe level: on Fixtures D and E the instrument *did* imprint on the object — it reported an accepted algebraic exponent (`negative_alpha_singularity`, `fractional_alpha_branch`) where the truth was a zero-alpha boundary / non-algebraic drift, i.e. it manufactured "real-looking" structure that was an artefact of a single finite-window log-log fit (`discovery_report.md` L104-153,186-205). The arc's response — `alpha_zero_boundary` + `alpha_unstable_window` + nested-window stability evidence so the probe refuses to export an algebraic sticker it cannot defend — is precisely the "don't let the instrument over-claim" discipline Q5 demands. This is on-vector for Q5 and consonant with Ax3 (no hidden guard rails), Ax4 (multi-field validity), Ax6 (zero is measured or proven), and Ax9 (false type stickers are worse than untyped failure): the arc converts a silent mis-sticker into an explicit, typed refusal-to-claim.

It is also a step toward Q6 (the tooling wall — detect-but-cannot-resolve). The nested-window stability machinery is a finer screening lens that lets the substrate say "this window is not stable" rather than emitting a confident single number — a primitive-level instrument refinement, even though it does not yet resolve *under* the arithmetic noise floor (confidence high).

The honest distance caveats (field-4 trend, not leaking into 1-3): (a) the work is on abstract alpha fixtures, not on Will's two-form GR/SR constraint pair, so it advances the *instrument* axis without yet advancing the *phenomenon* axes (Q1 what casts the patterns, Q2 why route matters, Q3 the doubling ladder, Q4 the boundary envelope) or Obs7 (precision scaling) — correct sequencing, not drift. (b) The transfer-function paper is cited as the theoretical reference for the iterated-log case, and the spec notes V3 "used slope-flow model comparison… BIC margins" for the same discrimination (`codex_task023_iterated_logarithm_discovery.md` L27-31); the V4 work re-derived its own strata rather than importing V3's model machinery, so the V3 mention is reference-for-which-problems-are-real, not a copied design — consistent with §5 discipline, flagged here only as a thing to keep watching. No divergence found; the arc is a tight, gated, observation-then-fix loop that ends pointed at the next planned step.

